java must be installed on your machine
ant 1.7.0 or newer must be installed on your machine
git must be installed on your machine

git clone git@github.com:chb/smart_client_java.git
cd bin
edit build.sh setting  -Dsmart_owl_path=<path-to-smart.owl-on-your-local-machine>  -Djust_for_challenge="challenge"
     to include all of the API, even parts not usefull for the "SMArt Health App Challenge" remove the challenge 
     -Dsmart_owl_path=<path-to-smart.owl-on-your-local-machine> -Djust_for_challenge="nochallenge"
./build.sh

cd ..

creates:
    src/org/smartplatforms/client/SMArtClient.java
    javadoc/index.html  and etc.
    build/SMArtClient-0.2.jar
    build/smartapp.war


To run the perscription reminder test, cp build/smartapp.war to <tomcat-directory>/webapps
start up tomcat
follow instructions in
   http://wiki.chip.org/smart-project/index.php/Developers_Documentation:_Getting_Started#Running_in_the_context_of_the_Developers.27_Sandbox
